Any thoughts on shortening a statement in the lead section as follows?

:<u>CURRENT VERSION</u>: {{green|Trump has made many false or misleading statements during his campaign and presidency. The statements have been documented by fact-checkers, and the media have widely described the phenomenon as unprecedented in American politics.}}

:<u>PROPOSED NEW VERSION</u>: {{green|Trump has made many false and misleading statements during his campaigns and presidency, to a degree unprecedented in American politics.}}

This would go down from 33 words to 22 words; it would preserve the most important bits (i.e., the level/rate of falsehoods is unprecedented) while omitting the unremarkable/obvious (the fact that these falsehoods have been documented - obviously they have been or else we wouldn't be making a reference to it in the Wikipedia bio).
